caption.text: "Son of a Peach" brew review: I didn't believe it was possible for a flavored beer to be good enough to take seriously as a craft brew, but this one is amazing! Son of a Peach is an unfiltered wheat beer with a mean peach finish that will knock your socks off. It's brewed by RJ Rockers (I believe to be located in Spartanburg, SC) and is a special seasonal brew. It was highly recommended by my dear friend @mrscaffeinated (who doesn't even drink) based on the reviews of her beer snob friends. I'm generally not a fan of wheat beers, opting for hoppier Pale Ales, but this is a new favorite. This brew is aromatic and smooth but has a surprising finish of peaches that you smell more than taste. A totally new beer experience for me. If you can't get this where you live, then you'll just have to come visit. Cheers.
